SIMPLE: hypochondriac
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hypochondriac
<hw>Hy`po*chon"dri*ac</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
affocated in the hypochondrium: cf. F. <ets>hypocondriaque</ets>,
formerly spelt <ets>hypochondriaque</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or
pertaining to hypochondria, or the hypochondriac regions.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Affected, characterized, or produced, by
hypochondriasis.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Hypochondriac region</b></col> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>, <cd>a
region on either side of the abdomen beneath the cartilages of the false
ribs, beside the epigastric, and above the lumbar, region.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hypochondriac</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Hypochondriac
<hw>Hy`po*chon"dri*ac</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A person affected with
hypochondria.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He had become an incurable <qex>hypochondriac</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hypochondriacal</ent>⟦br⟧
